      "beast_baseline": "hey i'm working on this embedded project and the heap just keeps climbing until it crashes. i'm using raw pointers for some of the buffer management. can u look at this and see why it might be leaking?\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n\nclass DataBuffer {\npublic:\n    DataBuffer(int size) : size(size) {\n        data = new char[size];\n        std::cout << \"Buffer allocated\" << std::endl;\n    }\n    ~DataBuffer() {\n        delete[] data;\n        std::cout << \"Buffer freed\" << std::endl;\n    }\n    void process() {\n        // do stuff\n    }\nprivate:\n    int size;\n    char* data;\n};\n\nvoid run_process() {\n    DataBuffer* buf = new DataBuffer(1024);\n    buf->process();\n    // i think i'm supposed to clean up here?\n}\n\nint main() {\n    for(int i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {\n        run_process();\n    }\n    return 0;\n}\n```",
